<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06284151 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06284151 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  OBITUARY; NAME; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  FORSYTHE, Roger, 36, head designer for the Perry Ellis Group, the men's wearcompany; Sunday at New York University Medical Center of lymphatic cancer. Mr.Forsythe, who was born in Missouri and raised in Texas, was recruited by thegroup in 1988 as vice president and men's design director. His assignment wasto restore the humor and verve in sportswear that had characterized theoriginals of Perry Ellis.;   GOODRICH, Benjamin Briggs, 42, mathematician andson of actress Olivia de Havilland; Sept. 29 in Paris of heart failure causedby constrictive pericarditis. Mr. Goodrich was the only son of De Havillandand had lived in Austin, Texas. He at one time worked as a statistical analystfor Lockheed Missiles andamp; Space Co. in Sunnyvale. He is also survived by hisfather, Marcus Aurelius Goodrich of Richmond, Va.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  DEATHS ELSEWHERE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     McMORRAN, J. Burch, 92, a career civil servant who helped design and buildsome of the most important public works projects in New York state; Sunday atEddy Memorial Geriatric Center in Troy, N.Y., of cardiac arrest.;  SCHAINHOLZ, Herbert, 66, an inventor and manufacturer of medical instruments;Saturday at his home in Teaneck, N.J., of stomach cancer. Among the inventionspatented by Mr. Schainholz is a device that counts and memorizes the number ofsurgical instruments used in an operation to prevent any misplacement of theinstruments.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911010  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  223  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, October 10, 199100284151,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Me